Package: ufw-cf
Version: 1.0.0
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: ufw, curl, systemd, bash (>= 4.0)
Maintainer: Malith Rukshan <hello@malith.dev>
Homepage: https://github.com/Malith-Rukshan/ufw-cf
Description: Keep UFW rules in sync with Cloudflare IP ranges
 ufw-cf is a small CLI and systemd timer that keeps an Ubuntu / Debian
 firewall in sync with Cloudflare's published IPv4 and IPv6 ranges, so
 that ports 80 and 443 are reachable only by Cloudflare edge servers.
 .
 Includes subcommands: sync, status, enable, disable, clean, and an
 interactive menu when invoked without arguments.
